==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: billfold
<hw>bill"fold`</hw> <pr>(b⟦icr⟧l" f⟦omac⟧ld`)</pr>, <def>A small, thin,
flat container, usually made of leather or imitation leather, having a
pocket of a size just large enough to hold paper currency and folded
over once to fit in the pocket of one's clothing; it is a type of
<isa>wallet</isa>, but having fewer compartments than the typical
wallet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Billhead</ent>⟦br⟧
